# Tech Stack

## Language & Runtime

- Python 3.11+ with `from __future__ import annotations` in every module
- Package management via **uv** (`pyproject.toml`, `uv sync`, `uv run`)
- Entrypoint: `uv run bot --url <URL>` (defined in `[project.scripts]`)

## Core Dependencies

| Package | Purpose |
|---|---|
| seleniumbase | Browser automation via UC Mode + CDP Mode (Chrome) |
| pdf2image | PDF page to PIL Image conversion (requires system poppler) |
| pytesseract | OCR on PIL Images (requires system tesseract) |
| openai | LLM API client (chat completions) |
| python-dotenv | Load `.env` for `OPENAI_API_KEY` |
| opencv-python-headless | Dev dep: template matching + OCR in tests/vision_utils.py |

## Project Layout

```
src/bot/
├── main.py      # CLI (argparse) + orchestration
├── browser.py   # SeleniumBase CDP mode, iframe Print PDF, form interaction
├── ocr.py       # PDF-to-text pipeline (pdf2image + pytesseract)
└── llm.py       # OpenAI chat completions

scripts/
└── launch_chrome.py        # Launch Chrome with PDF auto-download prefs

tests/
├── vision_utils.py         # Template matching + OCR (test-only, not used by bot)
├── browser_utils.py        # Shared SbAdapter, launch/connect for flow tests
├── conftest.py             # Fixtures: example_page, print_pdf_button
├── example-page.png        # Screenshot fixture for template/OCR tests
├── print-pdf-button.png    # Template fixture
├── exampl-pdf.pdf          # Sample PDF for flow-3-attach
├── flow_1_cloudflare.py    # Flow 1: URL + Cloudflare (make flow-1 / flow-1-attach)
├── flow_2_print_pdf.py     # Flow 2: Print PDF (make flow-2 / flow-2-attach)
├── flow_3_form_submit.py   # Flow 3: Fill + submit (make flow-3 / flow-3-attach)
├── test_ocr.py             # find_text_ocr on example-page
└── test_template_matching.py  # find_template on example-page
```

## Conventions

- All functions use type hints with `str | None` union syntax
- Test fixtures (images, PDF) live in `tests/`; `conftest.py` uses `TESTS_DIR` for paths
- Modules are flat functions (no classes) grouped by concern
- CLI arguments use `argparse`; `.env` loaded via `load_dotenv()` at startup
- All browser interactions go through `browser.py` using SeleniumBase CDP mode; never import seleniumbase elsewhere
- Browser lifecycle managed by `SB(uc=True)` context manager in `main.py`
